Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the descriptive complexity of LOGCFL using first-order logic and quantifiers. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity of LOGCFL and its subclasses. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with context-free languages and automata. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper introduces the concept of aperiodic nondeterministic finite automata. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the expressive power of different types of first-order logic.
